frameDefinitions: A Driver prepares a Vehicle for travel by placing it in the normal location for the operation of the vehicle or by detaching it from a place where it was held.
This frame contains words for types of noise which can be used to characterize verbal communication.
A Cognizer computes a Result on the basis of input Numbers by addition.   '
A Cognizer carries out an approximate calculation or considers some Evidence so as to arrive at an approximate Value for some Feature of an Item.
In this frame a Preventing_cause interferes with the ability of a Protagonist to complete an intended Action.

This frame consists of words that indicate that an Agent or a Cause affects the position of an Item on some scale (the Attribute) to change it from an initial value (Value_1) to an end value (Value_2).

listRoleDefinitions: This is the being, typically human, that prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion, and will control it once it is in motion.
The device--such as a car, boat, spaceship,. etc.--which is used for transport and is prepared for travel by the <fen>Driver</fen>.
Any expression which describes the location that the <fen>Vehicle</fen> has been stationed at.
The  <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Driver</fen> prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the <fen>Driver</fen> prepares the <fen>Vehicle</fen> for motion.
<fen>Speaker</fen> is the sentient entity that delivers the <fen>Message</fen>.
Message has a number of different realizations in this frame, including <ment>that</ment>-clauses, direct quotes, infinitival complements, <ment>for-to</ment> phrases, and NP Objects.
<fen>Topic</fen> occurs in PP Complements, usually headed by <ment>about</ment>.
The <fen>Voice</fen> describes the <fex name=''>Speaker'</fex>s utterance or other message-encoded production.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> where the Communication noise event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where an event occurs.
The person doing the calculation.
The <fen>Numbers</fen> that are used in the calculation.
The outcome of the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s calculcations.
The time at which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> operates on the <fen>Numbers</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Cognizer</fen> performs their calculation
The individual who considers evidence or performs calculations to arrive at an approximation.
The feature is a scalar property of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The position or area  on the <fen>Feature</fen> scale that the <fen>Cognizer</fen> concludes the <fen>Item</fen> occupies.
The entity that possesses the <fen>Feature</fen> whose <fen>Value</fen> the <fen>Cognizer</fen> seeks to approximate.
A proposition expressing the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s approximation of a <fen>Feature</fen>'s <fen>Value</fen>.
An open proposition for which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> seeks to approximate the <fen>Value</fen> of a variable.
The time period during which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> forms the estimate of the <fen>Feature</fen>'s <fen>Value</fen>.
The location in which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> forms their estimate.
The <fen>Preventing_cause</fen> is the agent or force who keeps the <fen>Protagonist</fen> from completing her or his planned <fen>Action</fen>.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the individual or group of individuals who have a planned <fen>Action</fen> which is prevented by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen>
The <fen>Action</fen> is the action or event certain individuals desire to bring about which is prevented by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the thwarting occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the thwarting occurs.
The person who causes an entity (Item) to change its positon on a scale with respect to some property (Variable).
The scale along which the <fen>Item</fen> ranges in value.
The entity whose position along a scale is being changed.
The force that causes the change.
When the event occurs.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the value of an <fen>Attribute</fen>.
